{"id":14881231,"mediaExerciseId":"dc073647-8d25-48fb-ae70-1844da656130","exerciseName":"7","chapterName":"10","chapterTitle":"Making Capital Investment Decisions","groupId":612341,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":341,"solutions":[{"id":6277420,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will consider the examine the different factors that come into making a decision involving the release of a similar product from the same company. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"When launching a product that is similar to one that is already being produced by the same company, different factors should be studied. \n\nFirst, the effect of erosion. Erosion is defined as the negative impact on a company's assets or funds. Creating an \"essentialized\" version of the book may lower the revenue being brought by the original book since some people may opt to just buy this simplified version. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Aside from erosion, the cost of production and marketing of the book must also be considered. Since this will be another asset, the storage space in factories may be limited since the sale of the original book may be slower. This means that there can only be limited copies of the book. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Despite the possible low cost of the \"essentialized\" version of the book, the negative effects it has on the company's revenue may not be acceptable since it reduces the revenue on the original book and there will be additional costs in producing and selling the new book. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"5cdd1553-2393-4791-8822-0aeba4304491","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881232,"exerciseName":"8","page":342,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"720e8a56-dc5d-459d-850d-440e619630cc","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-10-critical-thinking-questions-8-720e8a56-dc5d-459d-850d-440e619630cc"},{"id":14881233,"exerciseName":"9","page":342,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"41bfc574-7cd1-499d-a0b9-d5f3c1757ac1","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-10-critical-thinking-questions-9-41bfc574-7cd1-499d-a0b9-d5f3c1757ac1"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881230,"exerciseName":"6","page":341,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"529eec08-9efd-482f-bd73-0357d37358ea","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-10-critical-thinking-questions-6-529eec08-9efd-482f-bd73-0357d37358ea"},{"id":14881229,"exerciseName":"5","page":341,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"e56919ff-7356-4154-9